title <size:18>Amazon Locker Service - Class Diagram (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Customer orders a package, carrier delivers to locker, customer gets OTP, picks up package."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE — LockerService
' ====================================================================
class LockerService <<Singleton>> {
    - {static} instance : LockerService
    - lockerLocations : Map<String, LockerLocation>
    - packages : Map<String, Package>
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    - otpService : OTPService
    --
    + {static} getInstance() : LockerService
    + findAvailableLocker(location, size) : Locker
    + deliverPackage(pkg, lockerId) : DeliveryResult
    + pickupPackage(lockerId, otp) : Package
    + returnPackage(pkg, lockerId) : DeliveryResult
    + getLockerStatus(lockerId) : LockerState
}

note top of LockerService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "The entry point. Carrier calls deliverPackage(),
    customer calls pickupPackage(). This **Facade**
    coordinates locker allocation, OTP generation,
    notifications, and state management.
    Also a **Singleton** — one service instance."
    **Patterns: Facade + Singleton | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: CORE MODELS — Package, Customer, Order
' ====================================================================
class Package {
    - packageId : String
    - orderId : String
    - size : PackageSize
    - customer : Customer
    - assignedLocker : Locker
    - status : PackageStatus
    - deliveryOtp : String
    - otpExpiry : LocalDateTime
    --
    + getSize() : PackageSize
    + isOtpValid(otp) : boolean
    + isOtpExpired() : boolean
}

class Customer {
    - customerId : String
    - name : String
    - email : String
    - phone : String
    --
    + getEmail() : String
    + getPhone() : String
}

class Order {
    - orderId : String
    - customer : Customer
    - packages : List<Package>
    - orderDate : LocalDateTime
}

enum PackageSize {
    SMALL
    MEDIUM
    LARGE
    EXTRA_LARGE
}

enum PackageStatus {
    CREATED
    IN_TRANSIT
    DELIVERED_TO_LOCKER
    PICKED_UP
    RETURNED
    EXPIRED
}

note top of Package #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - Core models.**
    "**Package** is the central entity — has size,
    assigned locker, OTP, and status.
    **Customer** receives notifications.
    **PackageSize** must match LockerSize.
    **PackageStatus** tracks the lifecycle."
end note

Order *-- Package : contains >
Order --> Customer : for >
Package --> Customer : belongs to >
Package --> PackageSize : sized as >
Package --> PackageStatus : tracks >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: LOCKER HIERARCHY — Location, Locker, LockerSize
' ====================================================================
class LockerLocation {
    - locationId : String
    - address : String
    - latitude : double
    - longitude : double
    - lockers : List<Locker>
    --
    + getAvailableLockers(size) : List<Locker>
    + findNearestLocation(lat, lng) : LockerLocation
}

class Locker {
    - lockerId : String
    - size : LockerSize
    - state : LockerState
    - currentPackage : Package
    - location : LockerLocation
    --
    + isAvailable() : boolean
    + storePackage(pkg) : void
    + retrievePackage() : Package
    + openDoor() : void
    + closeDoor() : void
    + getState() : LockerState
    + setState(state) : void
}

enum LockerSize {
    SMALL
    MEDIUM
    LARGE
    EXTRA_LARGE
}

note top of Locker #C8E6C9
    **STEP 3 - Locker structure.**
    "**LockerLocation** is a physical kiosk
    with many lockers. Each **Locker** has
    a size, a state, and holds one package.
    Key rule: locker size >= package size.
    Locker delegates behavior to its
    current **LockerState** (Step 4)."
end note

LockerLocation *-- Locker : contains >
Locker --> LockerSize : sized as >
Locker --> Package : holds >
LockerService --> LockerLocation : manages >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: STATE PATTERN — Locker Lifecycle
' ====================================================================
interface LockerState <<State>> {
    + storePackage(locker, pkg) : void
    + retrievePackage(locker, otp) : Package
    + reportMalfunction(locker) : void
}

class AvailableState {
    + storePackage(locker, pkg) : void
    + retrievePackage(locker, otp) : Package
    + reportMalfunction(locker) : void
}

class OccupiedState {
    + storePackage(locker, pkg) : void
    + retrievePackage(locker, otp) : Package
    + reportMalfunction(locker) : void
}

class ExpiredState {
    + storePackage(locker, pkg) : void
    + retrievePackage(locker, otp) : Package
    + reportMalfunction(locker) : void
}

class OutOfServiceState {
    + storePackage(locker, pkg) : void
    + retrievePackage(locker, otp) : Package
    + reportMalfunction(locker) : void
}

note bottom of LockerState #FFCDD2
    **STEP 4 - Locker state transitions.**
    "Without this, Locker has if-else chains.
    **State Pattern** — each state is a class."

    "**AvailableState**: can store package.
    **OccupiedState**: can retrieve (with OTP).
    **ExpiredState**: OTP expired, return to warehouse.
    **OutOfServiceState**: broken, skip allocation."

    Available -> Occupied (package stored)
    Occupied -> Available (package picked up)
    Occupied -> Expired (OTP timeout)
    Any -> OutOfService (malfunction)
    **Pattern: State | SRP, OCP**
end note

LockerState <|.. AvailableState
LockerState <|.. OccupiedState
LockerState <|.. ExpiredState
LockerState <|.. OutOfServiceState
Locker --> LockerState : delegates behavior >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: OTP GENERATION — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
class OTPService {
    - otpStrategy : OTPGenerationStrategy
    - otpExpiryHours : int
    --
    + generateOTP(pkg) : String
    + validateOTP(pkg, otp) : boolean
    + isExpired(pkg) : boolean
}

interface OTPGenerationStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + generate() : String
}

class NumericOTPStrategy {
    - length : int
    --
    + generate() : String
}

class AlphanumericOTPStrategy {
    - length : int
    --
    + generate() : String
}

note bottom of OTPGenerationStrategy #FFE0B2
    **STEP 5 - OTP for secure pickup.**
    "When package is stored, OTPService
    generates a one-time code.
    **Strategy Pattern** — OTP format is
    pluggable. Numeric (6-digit) for SMS,
    Alphanumeric for email/QR.
    Add BarcodeStrategy? One new class."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

OTPGenerationStrategy <|.. NumericOTPStrategy
OTPGenerationStrategy <|.. AlphanumericOTPStrategy
OTPService --> OTPGenerationStrategy : delegates >
LockerService --> OTPService : uses >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: NOTIFICATIONS — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
class NotificationService {
    - strategies : List<NotificationStrategy>
    --
    + notifyCustomer(customer, message) : void
    + notifyPickupReady(customer, otp, locker) : void
    + notifyExpiring(customer, locker) : void
}

interface NotificationStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class EmailNotificationStrategy {
    --
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class SMSNotificationStrategy {
    --
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class PushNotificationStrategy {
    --
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

note bottom of NotificationStrategy #B2EBF2
    **STEP 6 - Customer gets notified.**
    "When package is delivered to locker,
    customer gets OTP via notification.
    **Strategy Pattern** — delivery channel
    is pluggable: Email, SMS, Push.
    NotificationService can use multiple
    strategies simultaneously."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, SRP**
end note

NotificationStrategy <|.. EmailNotificationStrategy
NotificationStrategy <|.. SMSNotificationStrategy
NotificationStrategy <|.. PushNotificationStrategy
NotificationService --> NotificationStrategy : delegates >
LockerService --> NotificationService : uses >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: LOCKER ALLOCATION — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface LockerAllocationStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + allocate(lockers, pkgSize) : Locker
}

class SizeBasedAllocationStrategy {
    --
    + allocate(lockers, pkgSize) : Locker
}

class NearestAvailableStrategy {
    --
    + allocate(lockers, pkgSize) : Locker
}

note bottom of LockerAllocationStrategy #D1C4E9
    **STEP 7 - Which locker gets the package?**
    "**Strategy Pattern** — allocation logic
    is pluggable. SizeBased picks smallest
    locker that fits. NearestAvailable picks
    closest to entrance. Add LoadBalanced?
    One new class."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

LockerAllocationStrategy <|.. SizeBasedAllocationStrategy
LockerAllocationStrategy <|.. NearestAvailableStrategy
LockerService --> LockerAllocationStrategy : uses >


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "We traced: carrier delivers package -> LockerService
    finds available locker via **Allocation Strategy** -> package stored,
    locker transitions to Occupied (**State Pattern**) -> OTP generated
    via **OTP Strategy** -> customer notified via **Notification Strategy**
    -> customer enters OTP -> package retrieved, locker back to Available.
    4 patterns: **Facade/Singleton**, **State**, **Strategy** (x3)."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | Carrier/Customer calls LockerService | Facade + Singleton | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | Package, Customer, Order, PackageSize/Status models | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | LockerLocation contains Lockers, each has size + state | -- | SRP |
    | 4 | Locker: Available -> Occupied -> Available (or Expired) | State | SRP, OCP |
    | 5 | OTP generated for secure pickup (numeric/alphanumeric) | Strategy (OTP) | OCP, DIP |
    | 6 | Customer notified via email/SMS/push | Strategy (notification) | OCP, SRP |
    | 7 | Locker allocated by size-fit or nearest-available | Strategy (allocation) | OCP, DIP |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Deliver** = Steps 1,3,7,4 | **Notify** = Steps 5,6 | **Pickup** = Steps 4,5 |  |
endlegend

@enduml
